___________________________________________________________________
DICTIONARIES 
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 1️⃣ What is a Dictionary?
    A dictionary stores data in key–value pairs.
Example:
code:   student = {
                    "name": "Yogith",
                    "age": 21, 
                    "city": "Bengaluru"
                    }

    Think of it like a real dictionary:
    ✔ Word → Meaning
    ✔ Key → Value
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 2️⃣ Properties of Dictionaries
    Unordered (in Python 3.7+, keeps insertion order)

    ✔ Mutable (can change)
    ✔ Keys must be unique
    ✔ Values can repeat
    ✔ Keys must be immutable (string, number, tuple)
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 3️⃣ Accessing Values

code:   student["name"]

note:   If key doesn’t exist → KeyError

Safer method:   student.get("name")
                student.get("marks", "Not Found")
syntex:         dictionary-name.get("search-key","default-output")
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 4️⃣ Adding / Updating Values
code:   student["age"] = 22     # update
        student["marks"] = 90   # add new
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 5️⃣ Deleting Items
code:   student.pop("age")
        del student["city"]
        student.clear()         # empty dictionary
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 6️⃣ Looping Through Dictionaries
-------------------------------------------------------------------
        Loop keys:
code:   for k in student:
            print(k)

        Loop values:
code:   for v in student.values():
            print(v)

        Loop key + value:
code:   for k, v in student.items():
            print(k, v)
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 7️⃣ Check If Key Exists

code:   if "age" in student:
            print("exists")
___________________________________________________________________

🔹 8️⃣ Nesting (Dictionaries Inside Lists / Dicts)
code:   students = {
            "s1": {"name": "A", "age": 20},
            "s2": {"name": "B", "age": 22}
        }
___________________________________________________________________

🧠 MEMORY TRICK
    ✔ Dictionary = Key → Value
    ✔ Fast lookups, fast updates
